#CHIP NES
#CLOCK 1789773

; NES APU Pulse Channels Test
;
; The NES Audio Processing Unit has 2 pulse wave channels (Pulse 1 & 2).
; Each pulse channel supports:
; - Duty cycle control (12.5%, 25%, 50%, 75%)
; - Volume control
; - Frequency modulation
; - Sweep effects
;
; Tests:
; - Both pulse channels
; - Duty cycle variations
; - Pitch sweep
; - Volume envelope

#TRACK 0

TEMPO 120

; Pulse 1: Melody with duty cycle sweep
c4 . d4 . e4 .

r4

; Pulse 2: Counter-melody (different duty)
g3 . a3 . b3 .

r4

; Both pulses together (harmonic interval)
c4 & g3 .

r4

; Staccato pulse pattern
c4 . d4 . e4 . f4 .

r2

#END
